Films | Sailing in Paradise, Wednesday 21 December, 18:00

Family: Putting on some chest-warmers, stirring your cocoa and falling asleep on Dad’s shoulder in a squall, takes you right back to your childhood. If this sounds idyllic then we salute your childhood. The certainly is as it turns out: your childhood; dignityless, rangeless, bankrupt of reason, boundless, moist, seaworthy, fearless and limitless at sea. Take a walk back into childhood, with on board each performance, the life experiences of the cast reveal how a child sees the natural world, and how the parents never see it the same way. Sailing in Paradise is a journey to Kipling’s tree play house, Lord Tennyson’s Arthurian labyrinth at Dover, and Hiawatha’s frame house – and the changing sea views that surround us today
